description: Track everything in Debian-based distributions
contribution_justification:
https://tracker.debian.org/docs/contributing.html#usual-workflow

We also accept pull requests on github.

repo_public_justification: Repository on GitHub, which provides public git repositories with URLs.
repo_track_justification: Repository on GitHub, which uses git. git can track the changes, who made them, and when they were made.
repo_distributed_justification: Repository on GitHub, which uses git. git is distributed.
version_unique_justification: The git commit id might be used as version identifier since anything pushed on the master branch is ready to be deployed. Disruptive changes are done in separate branches.
version_semver_justification: We don't have regular releases. Anything pushed to master is a new release.
version_tags_justification: We don't have regular releases. Anything pushed to master is a new release.
release_notes_justification: The software mainly powers tracker.debian.org. It can deployed for derivatives distributions but they would also be able to deploy automatically whenever new code reaches master.
release_notes_vulns_justification: No release notes due to continuous delivery.
enhancement_responses_justification: There are too many enhancement requests for the size of the developer team.
vulnerability_report_private_justificati: In Debian, all bug reports are public.
test_justification: We have unit tests and integration tests. Both are run via tox.
test_invocation_justification: ./manage.py test like for any Django project.
test_policy_justification: The contributing documentations enforces test-driven development.
tests_are_added_justification: Most commits touch both tests and code.
warnings_justification: We run pyflakes and pylint. We also use a hosted service: https://landscape.io/github/rhertzog/distro-tracker
delivery_unsigned_justification: python-apt does it for use (GPG signatures)
static_analysis_common_vulnerabilities_j: I don't think that pyflakes or pylint have rules tailored to find security vulnerabilities. Python is not a language where some constructs are inherently insecure so it does not make much sense.
static_analysis_often_justification: We run tox manually before each push. It runs pyflakes for us.
dynamic_analysis_justification: We don't have formal releases but the codebase went through such fuzzing when it got deployed on Kali infrastructure (at pkg.kali.org).
dynamic_analysis_enable_assertions_justi: The codebase will generate many exceptions when fed invalid input. But the end result is a user-visible error.
test_continuous_integration_justificatio: continuous integration is "manual" via running "tox" regularly.
discussion_justification:
Debian BTS on https://bugs.debian.org/tracker.debian.org
GitHub supports discussions on issues and pull requests.
english_justification: English is the language in use in this project.
hardened_site_justification: Found all required security hardening headers.

name: Portal Platform
description: The ONAP Portal is a platform that provides the ability to integrate different ONAP applications into a centralized Portal Core.
contribution_justification: https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Developing+ONAP
license_location_justification: https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Portal+Platform
floss_license_justification: The Apache-2.0 license is approved by the Open Source Initiative (OSI).
floss_license_osi_justification: The Apache-2.0 license is approved by the Open Source Initiative (OSI).
documentation_basics_justification: https://docs.onap.org/en/latest/submodules/portal.git/docs/release-notes.html
repo_public_justification: https://gerrit.onap.org/r/#/admin/projects/portal
repo_track_justification: https://gerrit.onap.org/r/gitweb?p=portal.git;a=shortlog;h=refs%2Fheads%2Fmaster
repo_distributed_justification: https://gerrit.onap.org/r/gitweb?p=portal.git;a=shortlog;h=refs%2Fheads%2Fmaster
report_tracker_justification: Jira is used to track issues. https://jira.onap.org/projects/PORTAL
vulnerability_report_private_justificati: Private vulnerability reports are not supported.
vulnerability_report_response_justificat: The project code do not have known vulnerabilities. However, the third party libraries that might have the vulnerabilities identified by NexusIQ scans are being analyzed and will be updated as and when the new versions are available. https://wiki.onap.org/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=45303158
test_justification: JUnit tests are used for java and Sonar tool used to measure the code coverage and NexusIQ tool used to check the license and security scans.
test_policy_justification: The code coverage requirement is listed as a developer best practice here: https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Code+Coverage+and+Static+Code+Analysis. So, when new functionality is added, tests of that functionality should be added as well to meet the code coverage requirement.
tests_are_added_justification: Sonar is used to monitor the code coverage and make sure that the test_policy for adding tests has been adhered to. https://sonar.onap.org/dashboard?id=org.onap.portal%3Aonap-portal-parent
tests_documented_added_justification: The code coverage requirement is listed as a developer best practice here: https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Code+Coverage+and+Static+Code+Analysis
warnings_strict_justification: Build systems run the compile with test flag enabled by default. So any failure in test cases will fail the ci and the merge request.
crypto_password_storage_justification: AES/CBC/PKCS5PADDING encryption algorithms are used for storing the passwords.
vulnerabilities_fixed_60_days_justificat: The project code do not have known vulnerabilities. However, the third party libraries that might have the vulnerabilities identified by NexusIQ scans are being analyzed and will be updated as and when the new versions are available. https://wiki.onap.org/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=45303158
dynamic_analysis_unsafe_justification: The project does not produce software written in a memory-unsafe language
dynamic_analysis_fixed_justification: Sonar reported issues are handled as low priority as of now, due to too many false positives in the report.
crypto_weaknesses_justification: We disallow SHA-1 or other insecure cryptographic algorithms.
discussion_justification: https://jira.onap.org/secure/RapidBoard.jspa?rapidView=33&projectKey=PORTAL&view=planning
crypto_used_network_justification: We use ssh2 internal to the cluster and TLS1.2+ for the external interfaces. But, HTTP port is still open to support few dependent components.
crypto_verification_private_justificatio: We support TLS certification verification before exchange of private information.
hardened_site_justification: // X-Content-Type-Options was not set to "nosniff".
installation_common_justification: The applications can be installed either using Docker via HEAT, or Kubernetes via Helm scripts.
dco_justification: https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Development+Procedures+and+Policies describes requirements for acceptable contributions and is linked from the Portal project page. https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Java+code+style shows java code style. https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Developer+Best+Practices
governance_justification:
ONAP requires both a Developer Certificate of Origin (DCO), and a Contributor License Agreement (CLA).

https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Contribution+Agreements
roles_responsibilities_justification:
The key roles in the project and their responsibilities are described at

https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Community+Offices+and+Governance

Current members are listed at

https://wiki.onap.org/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=8226539
access_continuity_justification: For Portal we have multiple committers and multiple contributors who are listed in https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Resources+and+Repositories#ResourcesandRepositories-PortalPlatform All committers have access and rights to maintain the code base, approve and review incoming changes and release a new version of the artifact. This will let the project continue with minimal to no interruption if one person is incapacitated. Also this project is controlled by the Linux foundation so we can add more committers if needed
bus_factor_justification:
The project covered in this report have more than 2 persons who actively contribute and maintain code. 
https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Resources+and+Repositories#ResourcesandRepositories-PortalPlatform
documentation_roadmap_justification:
Project Proposal and scope: https://wiki.onap.org/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=3247211
Roadmap for next release - https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Draft+requirements+for+next+release+-+road+map
documentation_architecture_justification: Architecture of Portal can be found in https://onap.readthedocs.io/en/latest/submodules/portal.git/docs/platform/architecture.html
documentation_quick_start_justification: Information on setting up ONAP can be found at https://onap.readthedocs.io/en/latest/guides/onap-developer/settingup/index.html
documentation_current_justification: Documentation is updated on a regular bases when needed. https://onap.readthedocs.io/en/latest/submodules/portal.git/docs/index.html
accessibility_best_practices_justificati: The project site is configurable for font size/colors.
internationalization_justification: In next release, providing APIs for internationalization features. https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Internationalization+language+support
maintenance_or_update_justification: All major releases are tagged in gerrit and the artifacts are stored with the release information on onap.nexus. So we can access all old versions of the artifact. If and when a upgrade requires certain steps to be followed they are being added to the release documents as needed
vulnerability_report_credit_justificatio: Vulnerabilities can be reported using the link https://wiki.onap.org/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=6591711 Currently we dont have any vulnerabilities reported, but the wiki page explains on how to report a vulnerability and how to report anonymously if you do not want the credit for it.
coding_standards_justification: Google coding style is used in ONAP https://github.com/google/styleguide
build_standard_variables_justification: The application does not create native binaries.
build_preserve_debug_justification: The application does not create native binaries.
build_non_recursive_justification: The application does not create native binaries.
build_repeatable_justification: All releases are tagged in gerrit(git), and the builds are controlled using jenkins. By providing the git tag information the same image can be build over and over again with same bit-for-bit result.
installation_standard_variables_justific: Docker containers are used for installation, so the conventions of the host operating system are not relevant.
installation_development_quick_justifica: All the components require only java and maven to begin with for a developer to quickly install and test it. Even for deployment using OOM and the right amount of resources, we can deploy the full Portal/ONAP suite in less than a day. The steps are documented in https://onap.readthedocs.io/en/latest/submodules/oom.git/docs/oom_quickstart_guide.html
external_dependencies_justification: The dependencies are listed in the POM.xml files of each project under respective repos. For example: Portal's root pom.xml - https://gerrit.onap.org/r/gitweb?p=portal.git;a=blob;f=pom.xml;h=e7f3360bd26b3acc901a659ec31d66d8bf8ac354;hb=refs/heads/master
dependency_monitoring_justification: We use sonatype CLM https://nexus-iq.wl.linuxfoundation.org/ and https://sonar.onap.org
updateable_reused_components_justificati:
Maven is used to manage external component versions, and the automated Jenkins build jobs will ensure the deployable artifacts are up to date with the maven changes.

Updating an external component simply involves making an update to the pom.xml file for that project.
interfaces_current_justification: We choose free open source solutions in every case and choose up-to-date versions of the components.
automated_integration_testing_justificat: https://jenkins.onap.org - on every commit, a verification job runs which runs an automated test suite. The code check-in cannot pass with out jenkins posting a +1 on the review.
regression_tests_added50_justification: We add tests in these cases.
test_statement_coverage80_justification: Portal is working toward additional coverage but lack of resources prevent us from acheiving it: https://sonar.onap.org
test_policy_mandated_justification: Contributing guide lines for development is recorded in https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Development+Procedures+and+Policies
implement_secure_design_justification: Portal strives to implement secure design principles. We encrypt data where possible, and run security scans on the code and its dependencies.
input_validation_justification: The project strives to validate all input, but there are few areas which needs to be addressed.
crypto_credential_agility_justification: Credentials are separate and can be replaced without code compilation, but still in the public repos.
